## 1. Purpose
This policy ensures that [COMPANY] can recover PHI and critical systems after data loss, corruption, accidental deletion, or ransomware, by maintaining encrypted, immutable, geographically and account-isolated backups whose restorability is regularly tested. It supports the availability of ePHI required by HIPAA and the recovery objectives in the BCDR plan.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all in-scope production data stores and the configuration needed to rebuild systems: [RDS]/databases, [EBS] volumes, [S3] data, [Snowflake], application configuration/secrets metadata, and IaC. It covers backup creation, encryption, isolation, retention, and restore testing.

## 3. Policy
1. All critical/PHI-bearing data stores **shall** be backed up on a defined schedule (§5) sufficient to meet the **RPO/RTO** defined in `resilience/business-continuity-and-../resilience/disaster-recovery-plan.md.template`.
2. **Backups shall be encrypted at rest and in transit** using approved keys (`cryptography-and-key-management.md.template`); PHI in backups receives the same protection as production PHI.
3. **Backups shall be immutable / WORM-protected** for their retention period (e.g., **[S3 Object Lock] / [AWS Backup Vault Lock]**) so they cannot be altered or deleted by operational roles or an attacker — providing ransomware resilience.
4. **Backups shall be copied to a separate [AWS] account and a separate region** (cross-account, cross-region) to survive account compromise or regional failure; the backup/vault account is access-restricted and isolated from production credentials.
5. Access to backups and restore operations **shall** follow least privilege, require MFA, and be logged/monitored (`logging-and-monitoring-policy.md.template`).
6. **Restores shall be tested on a defined schedule (§6)** and the results documented; an untested backup is not considered a valid control.
7. Backup retention **shall** meet business, contractual, and regulatory needs; backups containing PHI **shall** be retained and ultimately destroyed in line with `../asset-data/data-retention-and-disposal.md.template`.
8. Backup jobs **shall** be monitored; failed or missed backups **shall** alert and be remediated promptly.

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Platform Engineering Lead] | Owns backup configuration, immutability, cross-account/region copies, and monitoring. |
| [Security Officer] | Confirms backups meet ISMS/HITRUST and HIPAA requirements; reviews access and test results. |
| Service/Data Owners | Identify what must be backed up and the required RPO/RTO. |
| [CTO] | Approves this policy and material exceptions. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 5. Backup Scope, Frequency & Retention
| System | Mechanism [PLACEHOLDER] | Frequency | Retention |
|---|---|---|---|
| [RDS] / databases | Automated snapshots + PITR; [AWS Backup] | [Continuous PITR + daily snapshot] | [e.g., 35 days PITR + N months] |
| [EBS] volumes | Snapshots via [AWS Backup] | [Daily] | [N days/months] |
| [S3] data | Versioning + replication + Object Lock | [Continuous] | [N months/years] |
| **Snowflake** | Time Travel + Fail-safe; [database replication] | [Continuous] | [Time Travel N days + replication] |
| App config / secrets metadata / IaC | Version control + [export/snapshot] | [On change / daily] | [N months] |
[Set frequencies/retention to satisfy the RPO/RTO and regulatory retention requirements.]

## 6. Restore Testing
1. Restore tests **shall** be performed at least [quarterly] (and after major changes) for representative systems, validating data integrity and that RTO/RPO are achievable.
2. Tests **shall** be documented (date, scope, result, time-to-restore, issues) and feed `resilience/business-continuity-and-../resilience/disaster-recovery-plan.md.template`.
3. Test restores using PHI **shall** occur in a controlled, access-restricted environment and the data removed afterward (no PHI persisted in non-prod, per `secure-sdlc-policy.md.template`).
4. Failures or RTO/RPO misses **shall** trigger corrective action.

## 7. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Platform Engineering Lead] and [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 8. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Compliance is verified by reviewing backup job success rates, immutability/isolation configuration, and restore-test records during internal audit and management review. Backup or restore failures and any tampering are investigated per `../resilience/incident-response-plan.md.template`. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

